tool result:{'answer': None, 'results': [{'title': 'The 100 Best Songs of 2025 - Rolling Stone', 'url': 'https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-songs-of-2025-1235468614/', 'content': 'She’s ready to go to Paris and Malibu and “throw a party like McCartney with some help from my friends.” It’s a sparkling, disco-inflected pop song from a star in her sparkling pop-song era.—*Brittany Spanos*. On the LP’s standout moment, “Sugar in the Tank,” the guitars vault and jangle, and Baker sings about a longing so intense it’s dangerous — “I love you deadly as a heart attack/I love you halfway in a paper sack.” They nail the chorus like they know they’ve got a classic on their hands. Big Thief marry the commonplace and the cosmic like a 2020s version of the Grateful Dead.When Adrianne Lenker performed the lead track on their new *Double Infinity* a year before the album’s release, it was an acoustic tune in the vein of Neil Young’s “Helpless.” The band turned it into a gorgeous psychedelic swirl, perfect for Lenker’s lyrics, which begin with a missed flight and spiral into a road-trip meditation on memory, time, family, aging, and freedom.—*J.D.*.'}, {'title': 'The 25 Best Songs Of 2025 - NPR', 'url': 'https://www.npr.org/2025/12/09/nx-s1-5616663/the-25-best-songs-of-2025', 'content': 'NPR Music\'s list of the best 25 songs represent the upper echelon of our staff and stations\' favorite discoveries from the past 12 months. For those who want to dive deeper, please check out our complete list of the 125 Best Songs of 2025, which was handpicked by more than 60 writers and DJs from around the NPR Music Network of public radio stations. It\'s a deep and expansive examination of true romance, but it wouldn\'t be a Lucy Dacus song if it didn\'t have at least a *little* bit of ambivalence: "How lucky are we," she sings, "to have so much to lose?" —*Stephen Thompson, NPR*. But after listening to HAIM\'s "Relationships," I am also that alien, wondering what the word even means, what the thing even means, what the real deal is with relationships as the song jerks forward and back, questions itself then speeds forward, just like, well, a relationship. The French artist oklou\'s album *choke enough* is full of eerie, nostalgic electronica, but its last song, "blade bird," is a grounded outlier and also its best.'}, {'title': 'The 100 Best Songs of 2025 | Pitchfork', 'url': 'https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/best-songs-2025/', 'content': 'Here is where “I Ain’t Comin’ Back,” Morgan Wallen and Post Malone’s second blame-shifting duet, goes from a perfectly serviceable country radio hit to a great song: “There’s a lotta reasons I ain’t Jesus, but the main one is that I ain’t comin’ back.” It’s a damn near perfect line, one that’s funny and sounds like it was written and sung with a big ol’ shit-eatin’ grin. On “Bounce House,” the bubbly lead single from her debut album *Switcheroo*, the Los Angeles–based singer and producer born Angel Abaya crafts a spinning carousel with appetites bounding freely between a “Tommy” and a “Sally.” “I’ve been hoppin’ on the honest train,” she sings sweetly to the former, “Don’t love you less just because I got off without ya.” By the time the song ends in a chatter of giggly, excited voices engaging Abaya in a call-and-response about “drumming like a battery bunny,” it’s impossible to stop the giant smile from forming on your face.'}, {'title': 'Top 10 Best Songs of 2025 - YouTube', 'url': 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PwVJDq6u2gA', 'content': "Top 10 Best Songs of 2025\nMsMojo\n5740000 subscribers\n4167 likes\n335653 views\n6 Dec 2025\nTurn up the volume—these 2025 anthems owned the charts, the discourse, and our hearts. Join us as we spin through the year’s most unforgettable tracks, from “Golden” and “Abracadabra” to “Manchild,” “The Fate of Ophelia,” “Ordinary,” and “Berghain.” Expect massive hooks, daring genre mashups, and lyrics that cut deep. Which song ruled your 2025 playlist? Sound off in the comments! Plus a few surprises you didn’t see coming along the way. We also spotlight Chappell Roan’s aching “The Subway,” Raye’s brassy “Where Is My Husband!,” and Bad Bunny’s nostalgic “DtMF.” From Lorde’s euphoric “What Was That” to a spellbinding dark-pop return by Lady Gaga—and a breakout K-pop moment from Huntr/x—these songs defined the year.\r\n\r\nFOLLOW all our socials for more content here: https://linktr.ee/msmojo\r\n\r\nDon't forget to play our Live Trivia games at 3pm EST for a chance to win cash! The faster you answer, the more points you get!: https://www.watchmojo.com/play\r\n\r\nMsMojo is a leading producer of reference online video content of Top 10 Lists, Origins, Biographies, Commentary and more on Pop Culture, Celebrity, Movies, Music, TV, Film, Video Games, Politics, News, Comics, Superheroes. Your trusted authority on ranking Pop Culture.\r\n\r\nBadBunny, LadyGaga, TaylorSwift, SabrinaCarpenter, ChappellRoan, Rosalia, Raye, Lorde, HuntrX, Golden, Abracadabra, DTMF\n595 comments\n"}, {'title': 'Global Top 50 | 2025 Hits - Apple Music', 'url': 'https://music.apple.com/us/playlist/global-top-50-2025-hits/pl.4ce56ad1659d490cb125ed4fd9bfb6c3', 'content': "# Global Top 50 | 2025 Hits. Packed with all the best songs of 2025. Today's most streamed tracks and top songs - worldwide! Pop, Dance, Hip-Hop and Latin hot hits! 51 songs, 2 hours 52 minutes. * HITS 2026 - Today's Hits. HITS 2026 - Today's Hits. * HOUSE MUSIC 2026 | TOP 100 DANCE HITS. HOUSE MUSIC 2026 | TOP 100 DANCE HITS. * TikTok Songs 2026 | Viral Internet Hits | Trending Songs 2026. TikTok Songs 2026 | Viral Internet Hits | Trending Songs 2026. * Today's Top Country Music 2026 ☆ Top 50 Country Hits. Today's Top Country Music 2026 ☆ Top 50 Country Hits. * Rap Songs 2026 | New Hip Hop Hits🔥💯. Rap Songs 2026 | New Hip Hop Hits🔥💯. * Yacht Rock • 70s & 80s Soft Rock Classics. Yacht Rock • 70s & 80s Soft Rock Classics."}]}
