toolargs: {'query': 'best ways to relax while waiting boredom'}
tool result:{'answer': None, 'results': [{'title': 'How Not to Be Bored When You Have to Wait - The Atlantic', 'url': 'https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2024/03/waiting-boredom-frustration-strategies/677767/', 'content': 'The best way to lower the misery of waiting, then, turns out to be not to change the world but to change oneself. That insight can apply not'}, {'title': 'Anxiety Waiting: 5 Tips to Calm Down While You Wait - Psych Central', 'url': 'https://psychcentral.com/anxiety/what-to-do-when-you-have-to-wait-and-cant-stop-worrying', 'content': 'Soothing sensory tools and grounding techniques, such as music and deep breathing, can help when you’re experiencing waiting-related anxiety. Anxiety from waiting often relates to our perception of certainty and control, says Michelle Davis, PhD, licensed clinical psychologist in California specializing in anxiety research and treatment. Many people experience anxiety while waiting. ## 5 tips to reduce anxiety while waiting. Consider trying these tips to refocus your mind, relax your nervous system, and reduce the experience of anxiety while waiting. Deep breathing is an effective technique for dealing with anxiety while waiting, and it’s accessible anywhere and at any time. Creating a calming environment can also be helpful for reducing waiting anxiety, according to a 2018 study. “Many times, the beliefs we attach to anxiety can be more painful than the experience of the emotion itself,” Davis says. Implementing tips to reground yourself while you wait, along with mental health support, can help reduce the experience of anxiety while waiting.'}, {'title': "What to do when you're bored: 95 creative ways to reset - Calm", 'url': 'https://www.calm.com/blog/what-to-do-when-youre-bored', 'content': 'Sometimes boredom feels heavy — like you don’t have the energy to start something big. These small, playful ways to spark curiosity can shift you out of autopilot and make the world feel a little bigger… even if you don’t leave the couch. These simple, low-pressure ways to connect can soften that feeling and remind you that you’re not as alone as your brain sometimes tries to tell you you are. Fun is relative, but often, some of the most engaging things you can do at home are the simplest: rearranging a small space, playing music you haven’t listened to in years, or trying a new way of doing something familiar (like making your usual cup of tea), but with extra attention. ### What should I do when I’m bored and don’t feel like doing anything? Instead of trying to do something, try to simply notice how you’re feeling without needing to change it: Lie down, breathe, or even stare out the window.'}, {'title': 'Boost your brain with boredom - Mayo Clinic Health System', 'url': 'https://www.mayoclinichealthsystem.org/hometown-health/speaking-of-health/boost-your-brain-with-boredom', 'content': 'Join a club, try a new hobby, play a game, read a book or cook a new recipe to ignite your creativity and provide a distraction from boredom.'}, {'title': 'Try Doing This the Next Time You Feel Bored', 'url': 'https://www.oprah.com/inspiration/martha-beck-how-to-stop-feeling-bored', 'content': '# Try Doing This the Next Time You Feel Bored. They experience it as a signal that they could be learning, sleeping, playing or watching something more interesting; that every moment of boredom is, in a sense, costing them their right lives. Boredom is actually the feeling of being trapped doing one thing while wanting to do something else. This suggests that we\'re at maximum boredom levels when we\'re trying to stick with something while other things tickle the edge of our awareness. As ridiculous as it sounds, simply stopping is one of the most powerful boredom busters you can master. But so are theater lobbies before the show, long and boring checkout lines, and everyone\'s favorite, the john." Reading during such times not only occupies the moment, but gives you something to recall and chew on during things like dull conversations and meetings. Try this: When you\'re bored, just repeat the mantra "I accept" while fully experiencing the boredom.'}]}
